question: Highlight the parts (if any) of this contract related to "No-Solicit Of Employees" that should be reviewed by a lawyer. Details: Is there a restriction on a party’s soliciting or hiring employees and/or contractors from the  counterparty, whether during the contract or after the contract ends (or both)?
gold_answer: During the Term of this Agreement and for a period of                            twelve (12) months  thereafter,  the  Distributor (on                            behalf of itself,  each of its affiliates and each of                            their respective representatives) agrees that it will                            not  directly  or  indirectly  solicit  or  hire  any                            executive,  managerial  or technical  employee of the                            Company or any of its affiliates.
model_answer: 5.7 Nonsolicitation. (A) During the Term of this Agreement and for a period of twelve (12) months thereafter, the Distributor (on behalf of itself, each of its affiliates and each of their respective representatives) agrees that it will not directly or indirectly solicit or hire any executive, managerial or technical employee of the Company or any of its affiliates. (B) Distributor further agrees that it will not interfere with or otherwise disrupt the business relations between the Company or nay of its affiliates and any of their current or prospective customers, suppliers or distributors, during the Term of the Agreement and for a period of eighteen (18) months thereafter, nor will Distributor solicit any such customers, suppliers or distributors for the purpose of selling products or services competitive with those sold by the Company or any of its affiliates.

Practice problems? Overview: Intellectual Property Law - An Overview Intellectual property law is the legal protection of creations of the mind. Intellectual property law encompasses three main categories of legal rights: copyrights, trademarks, and patents. Copyrights protect the rights of authors in their original works of authorship, such as literary, artistic, musical, and dramatic works. Trademarks protect the names, logos, and other identifying features of businesses and products. Patents protect inventions, including new and useful processes, machines, articles of manufacture, and compositions of matter. The law of intellectual property is complex and ever-evolving. It is important to consult with an attorney who specializes in this area of law to ensure that your rights are protected and that you are not infringing on the rights of others.

Legal responsibility for the consequences of an act or omission.

#### Indemnification

A promise by one party to pay the losses or damages of another party, if certain specified events occur.

#### Tort

A legal wrong that is not based on a breach of contract.

#### Legal Fees

The fees charged by lawyers for legal services rendered.

#### Legal Expenses

Expenses incurred by a party in connection with a legal dispute, including attorney fees, court costs, and expert witness fees.

#### Legal Action

Any action or proceeding brought before a court of law to settle a dispute or to enforce a legal right.

#### Legal Proceedings

A lawsuit or other legal action, such as an administrative proceeding.

#### Legal Dispute

A disagreement or controversy between two or more parties that is subject to legal proceedings.

#### Legal Claim

A legal demand or request made by one party to another party, usually in writing, that the other party take some action or refrain from taking some action.

#### Legal Cause

The cause of action that gives rise to a legal claim.
